>>c4476d57-ac16-4362-8396-731e18c51b17
>What was the reasoning that they aren't using millchan's "temp id" thing?
If you mean the anonymous branch, it never worked. The developers hadn't realized anonymity was impossible with the way ZeroNet currently works before they began working on it. If you mean self-signed certificates, then it was disabled because of spam.
The **final** solution to the ID problem is combining seed ratio, proof of work, web of trust and captchas to make a CA that works with a ZeroNet plugin, but it would take a big programming effort to get it done.
ZeroID used to work with Tor Browser, but the gitcenter autist had to ruin it for us by spamming ZeroTalk with it on a power grab move attempting to prove nofish's leadership as inadequate, forcing nofish to block Tor.
Admittedly at the time I thought he was right to question nofish, but now with RMS being kicked out of the FSF and all the other SJW shit I see why nofish rules ZeroNet with an iron fist. If he moved it to a decentralized power model the corporate sponsored SJWs would take over.
